The paper deals with graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization, which are typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The focus on bipartite planar graphs suggests that cs.CG and cs.DM are likely categories, while the use of the isolation lemma and the reduction to matrix testing suggest cs.CC and cs.DS. The paper may also be relevant to cs.GT due to its application to game theory and matching problems.
